subject: Fixed a problem with neutron http policy check
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 2472, 'name': 'Doug Hellmann', 'email': 'dhellmann@redhat.com', 'username': 'doug-hellmann'}, {'_account_id': 6928, 'name': 'Ben Nemec', 'email': 'openstack@nemebean.com', 'username': 'bnemec'}, {'_account_id': 10780, 'name': 'Maruti Kamat', 'email': 'maruti.kamat@hp.com', 'username': 'marutik'}]
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-11-21 10:58:01.000000000', 'files': ['openstack/common/policy.py', 'tests/unit/test_policy.py'], 'message': 'Fixed a problem with neutron http policy check

When a rule "create_network": "http://127.0.0.1:8080/ or rule:default"
is configured in policy.json, create network with default values reports
a "Circular reference detected" exception.
The reason is, for unspecified values, default value of
neutron.api.v2.attributes.ATTR_NOT_SPECIFIED (that is, object())
is assigned by Neutron.
This creates a problem when jsonutils.dumps() is executed on a JSON
string that contains object(), thus reporting the said exception.
The fix replaces object() into empty value {} in the
dictionary, only for the policy check.

Change-Id: Ibd4859ed8c919ddb32cb75cc58c7f91d0e84a458
Closes-Bug: 1233707
'}]
commit_message:
Fixed a problem with neutron http policy check

When a rule "create_network": "http://127.0.0.1:8080/ or rule:default"
is configured in policy.json, create network with default values reports
a "Circular reference detected" exception.
The reason is, for unspecified values, default value of
neutron.api.v2.attributes.ATTR_NOT_SPECIFIED (that is, object())
is assigned by Neutron.
This creates a problem when jsonutils.dumps() is executed on a JSON
string that contains object(), thus reporting the said exception.
The fix replaces object() into empty value {} in the
dictionary, only for the policy check.

Change-Id: Ibd4859ed8c919ddb32cb75cc58c7f91d0e84a458
Closes-Bug: 1233707

commit_message:
Add pbr to installation requirements

Add pbr to the list of installation requirements so that it is installed
via pip before this library is installed, instead of with easy_install.
This avoids issues like Bug #1384919, and ensures that projects that use
this library as a dependency are properly installed.

Change-Id: I6c155370dbd01fe4748d5137bdf288e8d3e1a67e

commit_message:
Add pbr to installation requirements

Add pbr to the list of installation requirements so that it is installed
via pip before this library is installed, instead of with easy_install.
This avoids issues like Bug #1384919, and ensures that projects that use
this library as a dependency are properly installed.

Change-Id: I6c155370dbd01fe4748d5137bdf288e8d3e1a67e

commit_message:
dummy patch to let tox functional pass

Tox functional job currently will fail because there are no tests,
which is makes it a little hard to atomically turn on voting with the
test move. To trick the system we can make tox functional always pass,
then change the tox definition to the real thing during the sideways
move.

Part of bp:functional-tests-for-nova

Change-Id: Ic276522851fba6d1d95dd1f3bdde1d48935568a3

commit_message:
switch to use ceilometer specific connections

in Juno/Kilo, we added ceilometer purpose specific connections for:
metering, alarms, event. Rather than piggyback off oslo.db's
connection option (which gives misleading sql help message), we
should use Ceilometer specific connections.

Change-Id: I7703b73708a5807fb8de89fbb828f06b488acf69

commit_message:
Update Ironic jobs post-graduation

Make several changes to the Ironic jobs now that Kilo is open:
- voting on nova
- voting on devstack, devstack-gate, and tempest
- remove ironic*postgres jobs from non-ironic pipelines
- remove templates that are no longer needed

After the release, another patch will enable voting for the
ironic*grenade job on stable/juno.

Change-Id: I1a333f295f4498c24437a4b8280b15099d758d2a

commit_message:
Configure Cinder Volume service v2 endpoints

Updates the register-endpoint script so that it supports
configuring 'volumev2' endpoints. Also updates setup-endpoints
so that we configure both v1 and v2 Cinder endpoints in
the Keystone catalog for now.

This will help us transition to the new Cinder V2 endpoint.

Partial-bug: #1391603

Change-Id: Ic20d8df1d7bb559f6a2fe76f35c2e419477604eb

commit_message:
Update the Glance CLI doc for version 0.14.2

The glance CLI version 0.14.2 was released on Nov. 10, 2014 and the CLI
doc was not updated at the same time.

See https://pypi.python.org/pypi/python-glanceclient
and the 'Image Service command-line client' section of
http://docs.openstack.org/cli-reference/content/

The glance CLI doc has been updated to version 0.14.2 to include the new
'--profile HMAC_KEY HMAC' option.

Change-Id: Id83c23ffcd44ca49dcecefc605ed24befa0db661
Closes-Bug: #1396229

commit_message:
Changed get_nodes method in DeploySelectedNodes

* Added call of TaskHelper.nodes_to_deploy_ha if
  cluster is HA. It is exactly what nodes_to_deploy
  method does in TaskHelper. This method encapsulates
  the logic of appending all cluster controllers
  to nodes_to_deploy if user touches one of them.

DocImpact
Change-Id: Ie1853d49eec0293b760383a467d013dad58f69c1
Closes-Bug: 1386671

commit_message:
Update i18n translation for Nuage and SRIOV NIC AGENT

All the existing LOG.info, LOG.warning, LOG.error and
LOG.critical messages should have _LI, _LW, _LE and _LC
respectively.

Also, debug level log shouldn't be translated. This patch
set will cover the nuage and sriovnicagent directories.

Change-Id: Iadb99b802f204716ff8ebe1d7bc8892c597bb280
Partial-Bug: #1320867

commit_message:
Add systest for check readiness env

Scenario:
  1. Create cluster
  2. Add 3 nodes with controller and ceph role
  3. Add 3 nodes with compute and ceph roles
  4. Add 3 nodes with mongo roles
  5. Deploy the cluster
  6. Verify smiles count
  7. Run OSTF

Change-Id: I1d1ac09bd847a4578359b6e8ec895653def595fb
Closes-bug: #1391812

commit_message:
identity version resource and version fixes

Support for identity version and various version fixes:
* Added the notion of an unversioned service for a resource like the version
  resource.
* Changed all of the service filters so they could pass version through.
* Changed all the version resources to use unversioned services.

Change-Id: I92d6be9661560a8ced2648f1605fc3ffd8eeb91c

The first few sections of the 'Introduction to Ironic' document were updated to:
- mention that it is included with OpenStack releases starting with Kilo
- mention that Swift is missing from the Conceptual Architecture diagram
- removes Figure 1.3.1 "Deployment Architecture" and the text surrounding
  that for several reasons: it places ir-cond on the same host as n-cpu, which

Partial-Bug: #1353688
'}]
commit_message:
Update 'Introduction to Ironic' document

The first few sections of the 'Introduction to Ironic' document were updated to:
- mention that it is included with OpenStack releases starting with Kilo
- mention that Swift is missing from the Conceptual Architecture diagram
- removes Figure 1.3.1 "Deployment Architecture" and the text surrounding
  that for several reasons: it places ir-cond on the same host as n-cpu, which
  is not advisable in some situations; it suggests placing ir-api on a
  monolithic "Cloud Controller Node", but does not explain why this unusual
  choice was made; and it does not include any depiction of the physical
  servers which Ironic is going to manage, nor the IPMI network connectivity
  to them which is required.
- mentions that for security reasons, ir-cond should be placed on an isolated
  host, as it is the *only* service which requires access to both data plane
  and IPMI control plane.
- modified (what was Figure 1.3.2) deployment_architecture_2.png so that it
  doesn't include a figure number

Change-Id: Ifeeba636c9e7de65385e9f9c631709b2dd09e25b
Partial-Bug: #1353688

commit_message:
Undeprecate keystone::endpoint class

This class should not be deprecated in favor of
keystone::resource::service_identity as we have no way
to configure keystone::resource::service_identity through Hiera yet.

It would be the equivalent of deprecating all *::keystone::auth
in all our modules which was not our intention by introducing
the common keystone::resource::service_identity resource.

Change-Id: Ib424ac9b2c1e61e1e39fe56fd1adfe552110fcb8

commit_message:
Pass expected_attrs to instance_get_active_by_window_joined

This change sends the expected_attrs from the instance object
API down into the DB API so the client can filter on which
columns he actually needs to join when getting all instances
in a given time window.

The simple-tenant-usage API and _instance_usage_audit periodic
task are the only things calling this API and they already
provide specific expected_attrs so there is no risk of
regression due to the change. The DB API is backwards
compatible if columns_to_join is None, and expected_attrs
defaults to None already.

Change-Id: I3d8b5a1fd58783e465001bb5f10b5b87d69198d9
Partial-Bug: #1383469

Our experiments with unit tests for UserGenerator, especially those for
UserGenerator.create_tenants(), have revealed that it is the excessive use
of mocks:

    ...
    context = {"admin": {"endpoint": mock.MagicMock()},
               "task": mock.MagicMock()}
    ...

that leads to race conditions:
    http://paste.openstack.org/show/137037/

Closes-Bug: #1394158

commit_message:
Improve unit tests for UserGenerator

Our experiments with unit tests for UserGenerator, especially those for
UserGenerator.create_tenants(), have revealed that it is the excessive use
of mocks:

    ...
    context = {"admin": {"endpoint": mock.MagicMock()},
               "task": mock.MagicMock()}
    ...

that leads to race conditions:
    http://paste.openstack.org/show/137037/

Here, we fix the mocking of the task object that caused these race conditions
and unify the UTs code.

We also modify the UserGenerator so that it uses the more efficient collections.deque
instead of ordinary lists.

Change-Id: I8696287ecf9bc8bb44f67f70c81c6c93fdb8acbe
Closes-Bug: #1394158

commit_message:
Invalid GlusterFS share format error

When we provide invalid GlusterFS share format in GlusterFS shares
configuration file (glusterfs_shares_config), it will log a
Warning message in the volume log file, which not easily discover
able while debugging.

So, this patch changing Invalid GlusterFS share Warning message to
Error message.

Change-Id: I24d47dafc56490d40bd81256135f4b13fce5614a

commit_message:
VM in rescue state must have a restricted set of actions

Right now it is possible to pause, suspend and stop a VM in state RESCUED,
so after the state is changed, it's not possible to trigger unrescue anymore
since the original state is lost.

This patch remove vm_states.RESCUED as valid state from stop,
pause and suspend actions.

The vm_states devref is also updated to reflect this change including the
current reboot flow.( vm_states.RESCUED cannot be rebooted as per
today code)

This is a backport of 8ff170dc95bf3101fe38a2624e941bfa3b7c1138 .

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1319182
Co-Authored-By: Cyril Roelandt <cyril.roelandt@enovance.com>
Change-Id: I531dea5a5499bf93c24bea37850d562134dee281

commit_message:
AttributeError trapped when it won't be raised

In this block, AttributeError will only be raised if the type name
doesn't exist on self. If that's the case, don't cover that up.
We could be hitting ValueError or TypeError here, but just let them
happen as they will.

Change-Id: I69b4d1aaaff6e04d061ef7891bc88f9924c9973d

commit_message:
Remove ryu plugin

Ryu plugin was marked deprecated in Juno.
This commit actually removes the code for Kilo.

We (Ryu team) recommend users to migrate to ofagent, on which
we aim to concentrate our development resources by this deprecation.

DocImpact
Partial-Bug: #1391714

commit_message:
Unified interface for ScenarioTest and NetworkScenarioTest

Allows scenarios to use similar methods for Floating IP and network checks
regardless of network implementation done by Nova/Neutron

Creates floating IP helpers for Nova clients

Moves connectivity check helpers to manager.ScenarioTest to be used with both
classes

Change-Id: Id6a9feb7bcab811a5b5d4985397c419c02b4269a

commit_message:
Add gettext to the required package list

The recent commit d6f700db33 changed stable/juno devstack to
compile message catalogs during devstack.
However, gettext deb/rpm is not listed in the required package
list and it leads to devstack failure on fresh environments.
(Note that gettext is installed by puppet on OpenStack infra
so devstack never fails.)

The change is borrowed from commit 6518c0b88e in the master branch.

Change-Id: Id0efa75edde38640512a5ff6e0b5ef8d2ac5bb62

Changes in this release:
* Stable Juno release
* Fixed the default value of compress_offline parameter
* Always manages local_settings.py

* Fixed Apache config file default
* Added parameter django_sessioN_engine to horizon class
* Stops setting wsgi_socket_prefix since the apache module takes care of it

"}]
commit_message:
Release 5.0.0 - Juno

Changes in this release:
* Stable Juno release
* Fixed the default value of compress_offline parameter
* Always manages local_settings.py
* Added parameters to configure policy files in horizon class
* Fixed Apache config file default
* Added parameter django_sessioN_engine to horizon class
* Stops setting wsgi_socket_prefix since the apache module takes care of it
* Adds workaround for puppet's handling of undef for setting the vhost bind address
* Changes cache_server_ip in horizon class to accept arrays
* Switched the default log level to INFO from DEBUG
* Fixed the default MSSQL port in security group rules

Change-Id: Ie61702b6677e53cf78815ff356f09ab867333a08

commit_message:
remove nova pylint

This has been broken for weeks because of pylint upgrade changing
format. Pylint is becoming less and less useful as it doesn't do sane
things when presented with nova objects, so burning a test node on
every proposed patch doesn't seem incredibly useful if most of the
time it's not useful at all.

Change-Id: I4defa01608f651157120faf5a8eff70f74203baa

[{'number': 4, 'created': '2014-11-25 08:35:31.000000000', 'files': ['ironicclient/v1/node_shell.py'], 'message': 'Fix node-set-provision-state cmd's help strings

Current help strings of node-set-provision-state cmd is below:

$ ironic help node-set-provision-state
usage: ironic node-set-provision-state <node id> <provision state>

Provision an instance on, or delete an instance from a node.

Positional arguments:

commit_message:
Fix node-set-provision-state cmd's help strings

Current help strings of node-set-provision-state cmd is below:

$ ironic help node-set-provision-state
usage: ironic node-set-provision-state <node id> <provision state>

Provision an instance on, or delete an instance from a node.

Positional arguments:
  <node id>          UUID of node
  <provision state>  Supported states: 'active' or 'deleted' or 'rebuild'

Help strings "Provision an instance on, or delete an instance from a node."
and arguments description
"<provision state>  Supported states: 'active' or 'deleted' or 'rebuild'"
are different because we can also do rebuild.
This patch set fix this help strings to
"Provision, rebuild or delete an instance."

Change-Id: I21555a9dfc46b5539749de47e0cd4d403d8cd302

commit_message:
Add force_delete to safely delete created VMs

When Nova allows soft-delete operation, currently, rally cannot
deal with it and throws the exception when delete all the created
VMs.

Reproducing: (Nova enables soft-delete)
1. Run task: boot-from-volume-and-delete.json
2. It creates several VMs and volumes.
3. It deletes VMs.
4. VM states change to soft-deleted, but volume state is still in-use
because VM is not truly deleted.
5. It throws an exception saying that volume cannot be deleted.
6. The task is failed.

This fix adds force_delete when nova calls delete-server.
You can specify 'force_delete' in task configuration to determine
whether to use default delete action or force_delete action.

Change-Id: I56ac5c039b525a8b05960dfbfd3ff0cacec0aef6
Closes-Bug: #1394119

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-11-24 21:34:25.000000000', 'files': ['openstack/resource.py', 'openstack/tests/test_resource.py'], 'message': "Don't attempt to __get__ prop without instance

Doing something like Container.name raises an AttributeError because
we're trying to get the `_attrs` attribute of an instance that is of
NoneType. In general that's perhaps an odd behavior, but a primary issue
is that it hampers autodoc from being able to access member names on a
class, since it has to be able to import classes and access each member.
Since the members we're documenting are resource.props, which operate on
instances, we should bail out early if we're not actually given an
instance.

Change-Id: I45be106f88084325618df64e871b75accb36bf9f
"}]
commit_message:
Don't attempt to __get__ prop without instance

Doing something like Container.name raises an AttributeError because
we're trying to get the `_attrs` attribute of an instance that is of
NoneType. In general that's perhaps an odd behavior, but a primary issue
is that it hampers autodoc from being able to access member names on a
class, since it has to be able to import classes and access each member.
Since the members we're documenting are resource.props, which operate on
instances, we should bail out early if we're not actually given an
instance.

Change-Id: I45be106f88084325618df64e871b75accb36bf9f

commit_message:
[EDP] Improve Java type compatibility

Currently, EDP MapReduce (Java type) examples must add modifications
to be able to use from a java action in an Oozie workflow.

This bp aims that users can migrate from other Hadoop cluster to Sahara
without any modifications into their applications.

Change-Id: Iff6ff72439406b0cd454d6b1c5575f7b3e45a15c
Blueprint: edp-improve-compatibility

  http://rwmj.wordpress.com/2012/01/19/udev-unexpectedness/

commit_message:
Fixes Hyper-V Inspector disk metrics cache issue

Hyper-V Inspector yields a Disk with the property
'device' containing a dictionary. This causes an
exception when the values are cached in a dictionary
using the said 'device' as a key.

Closes-Bug: #1395807

Change-Id: I09b4ec2a37a6f7e6580a059517ab6e606bfc346f

commit_message:
Add timeout to all http requests

Currently, we generate lots of samples by polling data from other services,
but theses rest requests have no timeout limitation. We have observed that
some requests (for example, keystone due to openssl problem) may stuck for
over several days (maybe forever if we don't restart the service). Other
pollsters in same thread will not be able to work too. The worst thing is
that, when outside (keystone) service becomes normal, Ceilometer cannot
recover itself automatically, cloud operator needs to restart it manually.

So I strongly suggest that we should add timeout limit to **every** rest api
call, this is quite important to improve Ceilometer's robust and reliability.

This patch adds a new option named http_timeout, and applies it to almost
all http requests in Ceilometer project.

Change-Id: I76df2c0a9ffacb252e15edbb125e37ccb2aac4aa
Closes-Bug: #1388778

commit_message:
Update horzion::wsgi::apache for new apache module

A recent bugfix in the puppetlabs-apache module broke this module's
usage of vhost redirects. This patch updates our usage of apache::vhost
to use the new redirectmatch_dest parameter and pins the apache module
dependency to 1.2.0 so that the new parameter will be available.

Change-Id: I123b49eb54d7fd2908f09db03acacd1ba4f01492
Closes-Bug: 1390453

commit_message:
Prevent admin role leak in context.elevated

context.elevated was creating a copy of the current context then adding
'admin' to the roles of that context. This should be a deepcopy, otherwise
'admin' is added to the original context too.

Change-Id: I8ab00c88a8e76a14fb9f4ae96dfdb5f018fc2d0f
Closes-bug: 1386932

linuxbridge-agent: make vxlan unicast check more efficent

A list with the full range of vxlan VNIs (1 to 2**24) was using
over 300MB of memory. This patch uses xrange instead of range.

Closes-Bug: #1393362

commit_message:
Use standard assertVolumeStatusWait for volume detachment

Custom volume state detection method in test_compute_with_volumes
is unreasonable for volume detachment. Because in contrast to
volume attachment the target volume state ('available') is set when
all detachment processes have been finished.

Change-Id: I6d3d1186e73175fb25e2204088866cf53f61f4d5
Related-Bug: #1355285

[{'number': 6, 'created': '2014-11-18 22:03:40.000000000', 'files': ['specs/kilo/approved/iscsi-live-migration-different-target.rst'], 'message': "Support iSCSI live migration for different iSCSI target

Currently, Nova premises a situation which iSCSI target is not changed
before and after live migration. Therefore, if destination node has

specification. However, if each compute node uses same iSCSI target,

commit_message:
Support iSCSI live migration for different iSCSI target

Currently, Nova premises a situation which iSCSI target is not changed
before and after live migration. Therefore, if destination node has
different iSCSI target, the live migration fails in current Nova's
specification. However, if each compute node uses same iSCSI target,
each compute node recognizes all volumes in the iSCSI target and this
is undesirable situation from the view point of security.

Therefore, this spec proposes to support live migration of instances with
Cinder volumes among compute nodes that need to log into different
iSCSI targets to access the volumes.

For your reference, if iSCSI storages have features to manage visibility
of LUNs for each initiator within one iSCSI target, using same iSCSI
target for each compute node is not a problem. But general iSCSI storages
don't have such kind features, therefore they need this feature to
support live migration.

Change-Id: I9f0212cb74804e0122200ff543c46f1a91a39921
Blueprint iscsi-live-migration-different-target

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-11-13 13:52:50.000000000', 'files': ['designate/objects/base.py', 'designate/tests/test_objects/test_base.py'], 'message': 'Support Nested/Recursive Object Validations

This allows for Objects to reference other objects's schemas for use
by JSON-Schema validations. Lookups are performed via the Object
Registry using a pseudo URI scheme of "obj://" e.g.

    '$ref': 'obj://TestObject#/'

Is a JSON-Schema reference, pointing towards the root of the Schema

Blueprint: validation-cleanup
'}]
commit_message:
Support Nested/Recursive Object Validations

This allows for Objects to reference other objects's schemas for use
by JSON-Schema validations. Lookups are performed via the Object
Registry using a pseudo URI scheme of "obj://" e.g.

    '$ref': 'obj://TestObject#/'

Is a JSON-Schema reference, pointing towards the root of the Schema
generated for the "TestObject" object.

Change-Id: Id35c38536eb0d21bb66d3ca720d18e7f6ee733b5

commit_message:
Added disable_offload parameter

By default, we don't touch physical nic settings.
However, it is better to disable generic segmentation offload (gso)
and generic receive offload (gro). See ethtool man for details.

Related fuel-web patch: I24fdb63bab9166720862b4f6c96b90f6cd1d5f8c

DocImpact
Change-Id: I69fa29757557ed5337239031bf22d127e4a4edf6
Closes-bug: 1275650

commit_message:
Added 'disable generic offload' checkbox

By default, we don't touch physical nic settings.
However, it is better to disable generic segmentation offload (gso)
and generic receive offload (gro). See ethtool man for details.

Related fuel-library patch: I69fa29757557ed5337239031bf22d127e4a4edf6

DocImpact
Change-Id: I24fdb63bab9166720862b4f6c96b90f6cd1d5f8c
Closes-Bug: 1275650

commit_message:
In case of several plugins, nailgun should use the newest

For example Fuel has 3 plugins:
- name: plugin_name, version: 1.0.0
- name: plugin_name, version: 2.0.0
- name: plugin_name, version: 0.1.0

The problem was, when user enables a plugin on UI,
Nailgun enables all of the installed plugins.

With this patch, after user creates environment he can
enable or disable only 2.0.0 version of plugin.

If after environment creation, new version of the plugin
is installed, user cannot use this new version, he
should create new environment in order to enable it.

Change-Id: I51ba03166cd2a7379c6f0912d668265bf88a316d
Closes-bug: #1395342

commit_message:
Cisco N1kv: Fix update network profile for add tenants

This patch makes sure that while updating network profile to add new
tenants, it does not delete the older profile bindings and maintains
them, while adds only the new tenant ids to the bindings.

Change-Id: I862eb1c400e022334a2f6a4078425448bb144843
Closes-bug: #1379609
(cherry picked from commit c97069dc9a73344ebdc7b686133269850a81b3b2)

commit_message:
Add an "IPv6 Impact" section to the template

This change adds a requirement for an "IPv6 Impact" section. In the review for
Kilo priorities [1], the issue was raised around IPv6 being a priority. One
outcome was the thought to ensure new features are IPv6 ready from the start.
This change ensures specs have a section detailing how they affect IPv6.

I've also updated approved specs with what I perceive to be their IPv6
readiness. I hope the original authors can view these to confirm what I've
put in there.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/136514/

Change-Id: I6b12615d5d650ea55b8e78fd43c702af8f87b3f7

commit_message:
Move from using _ builtin to using glance.i18n _

The builtin _ should not longer be used.  Instead _
should be explicitly assigned from glance.i18n.

This patch does the following:
  (1) adds these explict assignments to any
      glance file that was missing them,
  (2) removes the defintion of _ as a builtin from
      tox.ini so that a pep8 failure will occur
      if _ is not defined,
  (3) removes calls to install().

This removes the last direct use of gettextutils by glance.
The indirect uses, via openstack/common, will be removed
in the next sync with oslo.

Change-Id: Ie54e8a67e747e022cc01022dfad35d89686bdfc4

commit_message:
Introduce a .z version element for backportable objects

This makes the object versioning code tolerate a .Z element to the version.
It is ignored for the purposes of triggering a backport, which means that we
can backport additive changes to a stable tree, denoted by the .Z element,
but which will not cause version comparisons to consider them incompatible.

There isn't actually much to change to make this work properly, aside from
avoiding a backport for only a .z in NovaObjectSerializer. Most of this patch
is actually just adding unit tests to prove that we tolerate the .z in the
version element in our compares, as well as confirming that extra stuff in
the data portion is ignored if our local object implementation doesn't know
about it.

Change-Id: Ic71268c036432c42f0d0ce7dfcb427abb65a24b4

commit_message:
Subnet delete for IPv6 SLAAC should not require prior port disassoc

With the current Neutron implementation, a subnet cannot be deleted
until all associated IP addresses have been remove from ports (via
port update) or the associated ports/VMs have been deleted.

In the case of SLAAC-enabled subnets, however, it's not feasible to
require removal of SLAAC-generated addresses individually from each
associated port before deleting a subnet because of the multicast
nature of RA messages. For SLAAC-enabled subnets, the processing of
subnet delete requests needs to be changed so that these subnets will
be allowed to be deleted, and all ports get disassociated from their
corresponding SLAAC IP address, when there are ports existing on
the SLAAC subnet.

Change-Id: I281f5a1553248e09174dc49d0a42aef4b5c44bee
Closes-Bug: 1393435

commit_message:
Fix wrong initialization of AuthPlugin for keystone v3

Ceilometerclient doesn't pass domain related arguments to AuthPlugin,
which will cause keystoneclient v3 cannot be used properly.

Change-Id: I2554a36f214c0eae61b7ba6b8580c41b8f8c6370
Closes-Bug: #1391122

commit_message:
Switch Puppet symlinks to be relative

This change allows rsync container to mount host
directory /etc/puppet to another path, such as
/puppet, without issues with absolute pathing.

Partial-Bug: #1395008

commit_message:
Fix timeout argument not treated as integer

Currently, if we specify --timeout 30 in CLI commands. we will get
'a float is required' error. Since we already specify timeout is
ingeter in ceilometer.v2.client, this patch converts CLI argument
timeout to integer.

Note, if zero is passed to v2.client, we treat it as disable timeout.

Change-Id: I213b6c24964095297cb4e87c25bb871ebd668bb4
Closes-Bug: #1391606

commit_message:
Test HA router failover

HA failover testing requires the ability for two L3 agents to
co-exist on the same machine. The following changes were made
to support this:

* Add l3 agent ability to simulate nested namespaces by suffixing
  each router namespace with '@host'. For example, if a router
  with id '1' is created, its namespace will be:
  'qrouter-1@host'
* Added test.common submodule which will hold common code which is
  shared between the different kind of tests (unit and funtional).
* Added tests.common.agents submodule which holds test-only agents, and
  added a test L3NAT agent to be used in the HA functional testings.

Co-Authored-By: Assaf Muller <amuller@redhat.com>
Closes-bug: #1374946
Change-Id: I2185fe276d9d32b34c407396e7ed5d6e2801340c

commit_message:
Create DHCP port for IPv6 subnet

There is a bug in dhcp agent code that when first port is created
in an IPv6 subnet, DHCP port is not automatically created.

This fix resolves this problem by removing the IP version check
in configure_dhcp_for_network method.

Change-Id: If3f405d367a7099d9f33d72d11ffcb7a393abe23
Closes-Bug: #1367500
(cherry picked from commit 1b66e11b5d8c0b3de0610ca02c3e10b6f64ae375)

commit_message:
Restore linuxbridge-agent compatibility

This patch partially reverts commit
15130cd5fd1688b8984d78136b97bb8de7c32b64.

This commit was desupporting ovs and linuxbridge plugins.
But the ML2 plugin can be deployed with the linuxbridge agent.

The current patch restores the linuxbridge agent configuration
file.

Closes-Bug: #1393429

Change-Id: If824185b22e22a1de6498f1f0f2742a279235675

commit_message:
Remove puppet run from static containers

Additional puppet runs have no impact on deployment
of rsync and rsyslog containers because they do not
change their configuration based on how a user deploys
their environment.

Change-Id: Ic5aac99620a8b6e24c5c5c2be9d246186df08a6c
Closes-Bug: #1395658
Related-Bug: #1382531

commit_message:
Replace sqlite with sqlalchemy

We used to have an sqlite driver and we kept it as the default value for
our storage drivers to keep backwards compatibility. It is now time to
move forward and use sqlalchemy instead.

Note that the entry points in setup.cfg are kept because we need them to
load the proper driver from pools based on the connection uri scheme.

Change-Id: I527c6ab15cc36e69d49a57a916ebc1296f73e3ce

it.

commit_message:
Set explicit route for VIPs

When VIPs are moved around explicit route for each VIP is
set to make sure that connections opened from local node to VIP
don't use VIP as source address - if VIP is used as source address
and is moved away then connections are stalled.

This explicit routes are removed when VIPs are moved to another node.

Closes-Bug: 1376200
Change-Id: Ie5d55fbe33231519015b313b1f9210ac3614266e

commit_message:
Fix recommendations post-POODLE

The POODLE attack compromised the security of SSLv3, and as
Bryan Payne notes in the bug report, we should no longer be
recommending its use.

This patch implements the suggestions from the bug report to
fix this, and add additional information on cipher suites.

Change-Id: Ife4ba2fb95682b064e913730a956cb0f77bb9c1e
Closes-Bug: 1389706

commit_message:
Use install_venv from oslo to fix no post_process issue

In a recent oslo sync commit Ieb73d5f799423fa8abf71634c86601ba6d32df2f
post_process() has been removed from tools/install_venv_common.py, which
is still called in tools/install_venv.py
Further investigation shows install_venv.py has some legacy distro
specific code, which should be removed at the time introducing
install_venv_common from oslo.
This change switch tools/install_venv.py to use oslo code to align the
effort as well as fixing original no 'post_process' issue.
Note: openstack-common.conf is not updated. Because the project name
variable in install_venv has to be modified after syncing from oslo.
That makes it not an exact sync but modification after sync now.
Change-Id: If58a11669348f039efec4d17a3a5b16ade9b9161
Closes-Bug: #1263940

subject: Make LVM Thin the default driver for Kilo
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 2243, 'name': 'John Griffith', 'email': 'john.griffith8@gmail.com', 'username': 'john-griffith'}, {'_account_id': 4523, 'name': 'Eric Harney', 'email': 'eharney@redhat.com', 'username': 'eharney'}, {'_account_id': 9003, 'name': 'Tom Barron', 'email': 'tpb@dyncloud.net', 'username': 'tbarron'}, {'_account_id': 9236, 'name': 'Jon Bernard', 'email': 'jobernar@redhat.com', 'username': 'jbernard'}, {'_account_id': 12369, 'name': 'Pure Storage CI', 'username': 'purestorage-cinder-ci', 'inactive': True, 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 12780, 'name': 'ProphetStor CI', 'username': 'prophetstor-ci', 'inactive': True, 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}]
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-09-30 16:20:04.000000000', 'files': ['etc/cinder/cinder.conf.sample', 'cinder/volume/drivers/lvm.py'], 'message': 'Make LVM Thin the default driver for Kilo

LVM Thin has been around for quite a while, but now
that Trusty has released; Ubuntu has the correct version
of LVM to utilize it by default (RHEL and others have had
the newer version for quite some time).

The Thin driver offers a number of advantages, of course including
efficiency, but also in terms of performance and eliminates the
need for things like "secure delete" (blocks are cleared on write
with LVM Thin if/when they're reallocated).

Opening of Kilo seems like a great time to make this switch, with
the latest LTS being out and used in the Gates as well as
ensuring we have a long cycle of testing available before the
next release.

Change-Id: Idc1288e4ed5508c33d09d1935e0c47efaac937ec
'}]
commit_message:
Make LVM Thin the default driver for Kilo

LVM Thin has been around for quite a while, but now
that Trusty has released; Ubuntu has the correct version
of LVM to utilize it by default (RHEL and others have had
the newer version for quite some time).

The Thin driver offers a number of advantages, of course including
efficiency, but also in terms of performance and eliminates the
need for things like "secure delete" (blocks are cleared on write
with LVM Thin if/when they're reallocated).

Opening of Kilo seems like a great time to make this switch, with
the latest LTS being out and used in the Gates as well as
ensuring we have a long cycle of testing available before the
next release.

Change-Id: Idc1288e4ed5508c33d09d1935e0c47efaac937ec

commit_message:
Add new table micro_states to cinder db

As part of Cinder explicit state transition work
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/110434/ along with
the transition table to know allowed states a volume
can transition to we will need to add a new
table 'micro_states' to the Cinder DB to keep the
information of the micro state in which the volume
is present currently. Also maintain a previous_id to
keep track of the point in time data that the volume
transitioned from to the current state. Useful
in making the decision regarding which state to
transition to next and also for debugging.

Part of blueprint cinder-state-enforcer

Part of blueprint valid-states-api

Change-Id: I10f71fbaf0b7ebcc791f19a110b44c72cf73958a

Cinder currently doesn't have use any options to mount NFS shares.
Although this works for most cases, it doesn't provide any feedback to
Cinder when things go wrong or the share is gone. This patch proposes a,
perhaps, saner default options to use that can be overwritten by the
user at any time. Here's the detail of what each option does:

soft -> report an error back when an nfs operation fails
timeo -> timeout for each nfs action
retrans -> number of times an nfs request should be retried

A note about using `soft` taken from NFS's manpage:

NB: A so-called "soft" timeout can cause silent data corruption in
certain cases. As such, use the soft option only when client
responsiveness is more important  than  data  integrity. Using NFS over
TCP or increasing the value of the retrans option may mitigate some of
the risks of using the soft option.

There's one case left un-handled by this patch. The options proposed
here don't handled mount operations that may remain hung. In order to do
that, 2 more options should be added: `fg,retry=0`. However, I think
these one deserves a dedicated patch since current mount failures,
AFAICT, are ignored or at least not handled correctly for this scenario.

Closes-bug: #1316075
Change-Id: I923ca5b4126b5c00eda28e17de0e15af289cf331
'}]
commit_message:
Use saner options for NFS mounts

Cinder currently doesn't have use any options to mount NFS shares.
Although this works for most cases, it doesn't provide any feedback to
Cinder when things go wrong or the share is gone. This patch proposes a,
perhaps, saner default options to use that can be overwritten by the
user at any time. Here's the detail of what each option does:

soft -> report an error back when an nfs operation fails
timeo -> timeout for each nfs action
retrans -> number of times an nfs request should be retried

A note about using `soft` taken from NFS's manpage:

NB: A so-called "soft" timeout can cause silent data corruption in
certain cases. As such, use the soft option only when client
responsiveness is more important  than  data  integrity. Using NFS over
TCP or increasing the value of the retrans option may mitigate some of
the risks of using the soft option.

There's one case left un-handled by this patch. The options proposed
here don't handled mount operations that may remain hung. In order to do
that, 2 more options should be added: `fg,retry=0`. However, I think
these one deserves a dedicated patch since current mount failures,
AFAICT, are ignored or at least not handled correctly for this scenario.

Closes-bug: #1316075
Change-Id: I923ca5b4126b5c00eda28e17de0e15af289cf331

commit_message:
Replace openstack.common.gettextutils with glance.i18n

1. Remove gettextutils module, and use glance.i18n instead.

2. Delete glance/openstack/common/test.py from tree, btw.

Glance do not use obsolete modules from oslo-incubator anymore.

Closes bug: #1381870
Change-Id: Ib9ef22a24f4fc9d6d935b7f7ee0eb23fb2215c1b
Signed-off-by: Zhi Yan Liu <zhiyanl@cn.ibm.com>

Parseable output format and --include-ids parameter are deprecated

commit_message:
Adapting pylint runner to the new message format

Parseable output format and --include-ids parameter are deprecated
and ignored in the pylint version used on the gate.
These functions are replaced by the --msg-template parameter.

This patch changes the runner to use the new parameter so that the
job can run properly on the gate

Closes-Bug: #1394606
Change-Id: Ia3e531923caa3f4e9a0dd03e0a4f5ef1a6d3dafb

commit_message:
Remove havana compat from nova.cert.rpcapi

Since we only support upgrading from N-1 to N, there's no need to keep
around this older upgrade related code.

Change-Id: Ie13f98da84f3d631efea2670fbc926b69b405284

commit_message:
Use common get_instance call in API plugins part 3

Cleanup v2.1 API to use common get_instance call which
automatically does exception handling. Although most of
the v2.1 API was cleaned up a while back, some recent
ports of v2 API code has resulted in some cases creeping
backing in.

Change-Id: I8271a2805fe9fdfae40df43183a5251fddbe4c13

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-11-24 16:08:39.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/unit/compute/test_tracker.py'], 'message': "Adds new RT unit tests for _sync_compute_node

Adds new unit tests for the resource tracker's _sync_compute_node()
method. These new unit tests should make the objectification of the

Adds new RT unit tests for _sync_compute_node

Adds new unit tests for the resource tracker's _sync_compute_node()
method. These new unit tests should make the objectification of the
resource tracker easier to do, since the old unit tests in
test_resource_tracker.py are brittle and hard to change.

commit_message:
Test message delete when claim expires

The patch adds a test for message deletion after a claim has expired.
The result of the test is that the message should be deleted.

Unfortunately, some issues related to the state of the sqlalchemy driver
make it quite hard for this test to work there without further changes.
I'm proposing this patch with some skips in place for the scenarios
where sqlalchemy is required, I'll propose a follow up patch to fix
those issues and enable these tests.

Closes-bug: #1369536

Change-Id: Icb12eed18c37455ad3528fa6a84fb8f2d8fcf19f

commit_message:
Blueprint for implementing the V2 API using the V3 API code

This is a proposed blueprint for implementing the V2 API (V2.1)
using the V3 API code base. From a user's point of view it would
be identical to the V2 API with the exception that it has much
better input validation.

Part of blueprint v2-on-v3-api

Change-Id: Id755f1f49c41df89c06ef2496e261d49bdd09ceb

commit_message:
Determine environment version based requirement files

It is painful to increment the venv version manually because
requirements.txt and test-requirements.txt are now updated by cron job.
This commit changes run_tests.sh to just store two requirements
files to .venv/environments file and check if it is up-to-date.
(Note that the environment cache file is moved to .venv directory
as there is no reason to store it in the top directory.)

Closes-Bug: #1376485
Change-Id: Ie44ccf6e2e65890baca3f316468254b600c518b1

commit_message:
Ensure Replication Tests do not use a stale token

Fixed the replication tests to re-authenticate the common test dbaas
client in order to ensure that we do not use a stale auth_token when
running the replication tests.

Change-Id: I37a2a4b7dca056e84b48c66cbe3b8c8fb6a2f1db
Closes-bug: 1394831

commit_message:
Eliminate unnecessary indirection in L3 agent

These indirections serve no useful purpose.  Normally, I wouldn't
bother to change them but these make other refactoring efforts a bit
more of a pain.

Change-Id: Ia73c93eb2eaa81d5772b3e0178fdf18f0c275b4c

commit_message:
Catch NoResultFound in _get_policy_profile_by_name

Add try-except in _get_policy_profile_by_name to raise
proper PolicyProfileNameNotFound if profile not found in
database.

Also unittest is added.

Closes-bug: #1393399

Change-Id: I3ab50a6870ff77a95e0977c75255e9cbd7286fbb

commit_message:
Make some pkg-map errors soft

An app using pkg-map (like package-installs) might want to distinguish
between a hard error (invalid pkg-map file) and a soft error (no
mapping found). Currently this is not possible because we only return
with error values of 1.

Also printing error messages to stderror so we can still make use of
stdout data during a soft error.

Change-Id: I8bef56d3a74e8530afb8c58ac50ca3e9f7700639

commit_message:
Check python with flake8 instead of dib-lint

We check python files with dib-lint rather than flake8 which have
conflicting opinions. This means weve been (forcibly) writing non pep8
python.

Also fixing pep8 issues so tests pass.

Change-Id: Idc9db40334f6e15738a7802c06697270df68741c

commit_message:
Adapting pylint runner to the new message format

Pareseable output format and --include-ids parameter are deprecated
and ignored in the pylint version used on the gate.
These functions are replaced by the --msg-template parameter.

This patch changes the runner to use the new parameter so that the
job can run properly on the gate

Closes-Bug: #1394606
Change-Id: I1de424bae4c2b634cd0bc804cb7e81624c96a195

commit_message:
Add WSGIPassAuthorization to OAuth docs

OAuth headers will not be passed in if operating Keystone under
Apache. Mention this in the docs that are used to enable OAuth,
so a deployer can know it's a configuration setting in mod_wsgi.

Partial-Bug: #1392584

commit_message:
DO NOT MERGE: log an error when vgs/lvs takes more than 60 secs

We're seeing hangs in the gate where volumes are deleted from disk and
then a minute later the volume status is finally 'deleted', which is
making tempest timeout on tear down.

We've noticed that vgs can sometimes take over 2 minutes, when normally
it only takes ~1 second.  So log an error when this happens and we can
start looking at logstash trends on the errors.

Also seeing lvs taking a long time, so debug around that also.

Related-Bug: #1373513

Change-Id: Ie5682e1152a90b3167ff41716c4148fe45d8a85b

[{'number': 5, 'created': '2014-10-16 21:21:57.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/brick/local_dev/lvm.py'], 'message': "Log a warning when getting lvs and vgs takes longer than 60 seconds

We know something is causing lvs/vgs commands to block while deleting a
volume and this is causing Tempest to timeout while waiting for the
volume to be deleted.  What we don't have right now is very good
(specific) logging when this happens, unless we get messages in syslog
for lvm tasks taking more than 120 seconds, but that doesn't always
happen when we see the volume delete timeout in Tempest.

This patch adds a check for when getting logical volumes and volume
groups takes longer than 60 seconds and logs a warning if that happens.
This is helpful in production also because the default interval for
periodic tasks is 60 seconds so having these take longer than that time
could cause periodic tasks to block up on each other and you'll get
warnings from the FixedIntervalLoopingCall in oslo which is controlling
the task runs.

Related-Bug: #1373513

Change-Id: I7ac5ddbbd9bda7744db33f0bb8d56879301f5538
"}]
commit_message:
Log a warning when getting lvs and vgs takes longer than 60 seconds

We know something is causing lvs/vgs commands to block while deleting a
volume and this is causing Tempest to timeout while waiting for the
volume to be deleted.  What we don't have right now is very good
(specific) logging when this happens, unless we get messages in syslog
for lvm tasks taking more than 120 seconds, but that doesn't always
happen when we see the volume delete timeout in Tempest.

This patch adds a check for when getting logical volumes and volume
groups takes longer than 60 seconds and logs a warning if that happens.
This is helpful in production also because the default interval for
periodic tasks is 60 seconds so having these take longer than that time
could cause periodic tasks to block up on each other and you'll get
warnings from the FixedIntervalLoopingCall in oslo which is controlling
the task runs.

Related-Bug: #1373513

Change-Id: I7ac5ddbbd9bda7744db33f0bb8d56879301f5538

commit_message:
Python 2.6 is end-of-life

Python 2.6 is end-of-life, and we should be recommending Python 2.7.

This patch updates two of the three places Python 2.6 was referred to
in the documentation, removing the reference to 2.6 but keeping the
2.7 reference. The final place is in the debian packages section of
the install guide, which notes several issues with Python 2.7 that
could now be solved. If this is the case, this entire section should
probably be removed.

Change-Id: I8c4043d180bc47de2afc40ce73640982f4c2f663

commit_message:
added reset_state and force_delete for backup

users and admin can delete the backup only if, it is in
available and error state. for any reason if it struck in
any other state, we can't remove/delete that.

for volume and snapshot admin can delete the files either
by using force-delete or by changing the state explicitly.
for backup these commands are not available.

so added force_delete and reset_state for backup only for admins.

usage of the commands:
backup-force-delete:
cinder backup-force-delete <backup>

Attempts forced Removal of backup(s), regardsless of state(s).

Positional arguments:
  <backup>  Name or ID of the backup to delete.

backup-reset-state:
cinder backup-reset-state [--state <state>] <backup> [<backup> ...]

Explicitly update the state of a backup.

Positional arguments:
  <backup>         Name or ID of the backup to modify.

Optional arguments:
  --state <state>  Indicate which state to assign the backup. Options include
                   available, error, creating, deleting, error_deleting. If no
                   state is provided, available will be used.

Change-Id: I726d77fc55c5c877fd6fb952c1ccb8a2a7bd93a1
Closes-Bug: #1279764

commit_message:
added token + service_url based authentication

from keystone service, we can get the token and service endpoints by
 using single REST token-get call. this token will be useful for
next 24h, so no future keystone communication require until the token
 expires. In cinder client, no option to provide this token and
service url via CLI commands. so two command line options
(--os-auth-token and --os-volume-url) added in cinder client.

the usage of the options are,
--os-auth-token <os-auth-token>
                        Defaults to env[OS_AUTH_TOKEN]
--os-volume-url <os-volume-url>
                        Use this API endpoint instead of service catalog

Change-Id: I3af7b75657805495806c1450b809d9b41afc3d06
Closes-Bug: #1197746

commit_message:
Authenticate through keystoneclient instead of keystone

Cinderclient should use python-keystoneclient to obtain token and
endpoint, it allow to have access to the latest version of keystone
api and get rid of duplicating of keystone logic.

Usage of keystoneclient allow not to process applying for token in
cinderclient, service catalog also is parsed inside of keystone and
cinderclient get only one suitable endpoint.

Logic of trust authentication also implemented in keystone,
so there is no need to process proxy tokens and tenants inside
cinderclient.

Change-Id: Ibc951681931e0acd1c24c3225766bb02af609c39
Related-Bug: #1154809

commit_message:
Add volume ACL support

Add new CLI functions:
    permission-delete   Undo a volume permission.
    permission-get      Get volume permission.
    permission-list     List all the volume permissions.
    permission-set      Creates a volume permission or updates if it
exists.
    permission-show     Show details about a volume permission.

blueprint volume-acl

Change-Id: I1419c5ed0cbdc4d7d540912b9d6a35e8f1ae9f02

commit_message:
TLS Data Security Overview

Here we define the overall strategy for dealing with secure TLS data
in Octavia. There are several areas that need attention, and they are
detailed in this spec. Barbican will be our default secure storage and
certificate signing service, but the interfaces should remain generic.

Sequence diagrams now included.

Change-Id: Icbbea8e37af0ce13fd959543403f2b01b8c7d17b
Implements: blueprint tls-data-security

commit_message:
Sleep several seconds on image service is executed

Sleep several seconds when doing action for glance-api and
glance-registry service to avoid service start failure caused by some
interruption such as glance-manage db_sync.

More details can be seen in
https://bugs.launchpad.net/openstack-chef/+bug/1331987.

Change-Id: Ie067813203547b88d556b209aa70dc8e197f4643
Closes-Bug: #1331987

This patch drops the usage of the RpcProxy compatibility class from
the bigswitch plugin.  The equivalent usage of oslo.messaging APIs is

Note that there is one very minor functional change included.  The
previous code set the base version to '1.1'.  It should be '1.0'.  The

commit_message:
Drop RpcProxy usage from bigswitch plugin

This patch drops the usage of the RpcProxy compatibility class from
the bigswitch plugin.  The equivalent usage of oslo.messaging APIs is
now used instead.

Note that there is one very minor functional change included.  The
previous code set the base version to '1.1'.  It should be '1.0'.  The
proper pattern to use is to set the base version on the client side to
be the initial version of the API (X.0).  Then, any methods that
require a newer version need to specify it.  In this case, verison
'1.1' was the security group methods, and those specify '1.1' as you
would expect.

Part of blueprint drop-rpc-compat.

Change-Id: I695d2a26db9c01b0be65b11cd4e4063567b5f20d

commit_message:
Release 5.0.0 - Juno

Changes in this release:
* Added heat::policy to control policy.json
* Deprecated the sql_connection parameter for database_connection parameter
* Adds parameters to configure deferred authentication method in heat::engine in accordance with new Juno defaults
* Bumped stdlib dependency to >=4.0.0
* Added parameters to control whether to configure users
* Added manage_service parameters to various classes to control whether the service was managed, as well as added enabled parameters where not already present
* Added the ability to override the keystone service name in keystone::auth
* Migrated the heat::db::mysql class to use openstacklib::db::mysql and deprecated the mysql_module parameter

Change-Id: I1eb3c5f278c1ff348fca3173c979cab2945e7a54

commit_message:
Make the REST API fully asynchronous

Today, Ironic's REST API blocks on many RPC calls to the conductor
service, which leads to significant scalability problems.
This proposal is to make Ironic's REST API asynchronous with regard
to the work performed by the conductor and drivers.

Change-Id: I3aec0dea6a7bab7a19abce11a275bef7c8a258f6

commit_message:
Design spec for iLO driver for firmware settings

The HP iLO subsystem is a standard component of
HP ProLiant servers that simplifies initial
server setup, server health monitoring, power
and thermal optimization, and remote server
administration.

This proposal adds support for firmware
settings interfaces introduced in
base.ManagementInterface to iLO client python
library to support HP Proliant servers using iLO.

Change-Id: I66c444571b3d4343afa957e1b3f617c8a07b1328

commit_message:
Release 5.0.0 - Juno

Changes in this release:
* Added neutron::policy to control policy.json
* Added parameter allow_automatic_l3agent_failover to neutron::agents::l3
* Added parameter metadata_memory_cache_ttl to neutron::agents::metadata
* Added l3_ext as a provider_network_type property for neutron_network type
* Changed user_group parameter in neutron::agents::lbaas to have different defaults depending on operating system
* Changed openswan package to libreswan for RHEL 7 for vpnaas
* Ensured neutron package was installed before nova_admin_tenant_id_setter is called
* Added api_extensions_path parameter to neutron class
* Added database tuning parameters
* Changed management of file lines in /etc/default/neutron-server only for Ubuntu
* Add parameters to enable DVR and HA support in neutron::agents::l3 for Juno
* Fixed meaning of manage_service parameter in neutron::agents::ovs
* Made keystone user creation optional when creating a service
* Fixed the enable_dhcp property of neutron_subnet
* Added the ability to override the keystone service name in neutron::keystone::auth
* Fixed bug in parsing allocation pools in neutron_subnet type
* Added relationship to refresh neutron-server when nova_admin_tenant_id_setter changes
* Migrated the neutron::db::mysql class to use openstacklib::db::mysql and deprecated the mysql_module parameter
* Fixed the relationship between the HA proxy package and the neutron-lbaas-agent package
* Added kombu_reconnect_delay parameter to neutron class
* Fixed plugin.ini error when cisco class is used
* Fixed relationship between vs_pridge types and the neutron-plugin-ovs service
* Added neutron::agents::n1kv_vem to deploy N1KV VEM
* Added SSL support for nova_admin_tenant_id_setter
* Fixed relationship between neutron-server package and neutron_plugin_ml2 types
* Stopped puppet from trying to manage the ovs cleanup service
* Deprecated the network_device_mtu parameter in neutron::agents::l3 and moved it to the neutron class
* Added vpnaas_agent_package parameter to neutron::services::fwaas to install the vpnaas agent package

Change-Id: Ia9c491db751cce07c67236ed5ccfe2fb73e782ba

commit_message:
Release 5.0.0 - Juno

Changes in this release:
* Updated token driver, logging, and ldap config parameters for Juno
* Changed admin_roles parameter to accept an array in order to configure multiple admin roles
* Installs python-ldappool package for ldap
* Added new parameters to keystone class to configure pki signing
* Changed keystone class to inherit from keystone::params
* Changed pki_setup to run regardless of token provider
* Made UUID the default token provider
* Made keystone_user_role idempotent
* Added parameters to control whether to configure users
* Stopped managing _member_ role since it is created automatically
* Stopped overriding token_flush log file
* Changed the usage of admin_endpoint to not include the API version
* Allowed keystone_user_role to accept email as username
* Added ability to set up keystone using Apache mod_wsgi
* Migrated the keystone::db::mysql class to use openstacklib::db::mysql and deprecated the mysql_module parameter
* Installs python-memcache when using token driver memcache
* Enabled setting cert and key paths for PKI token signing
* Added parameters for SSL communication between keystone and rabbitmq
* Added parameter ignore_default_tenant to keystone::role::admin
* Added parameter service_provider to keystone class
* Added parameters for service validation to keystone class

Change-Id: Ib280f684c8babf40df51d62bb21497c88ba3fd29

commit_message:
Make get_next_device_name() handle an instance object

This utility method is passed an object, but does things that assume it
is a dict. This fixes that, and updates the tests to match.

commit_message:
Don't run a query to check if the network exists

If the network does not exist, the query that inserts the port will
fail with a foreign key constraint failure.  This code is an attempt
to detect that and throw the NetworkNotFound exception when it is
caught.  This accomplishes the same goal as running
self._get_network(...) in the old code but without the extra query in
the non-exceptional case.  The non-exceptional case makes up the vast
majority of the times through this code path.

The old code doesn't use the result of the extra query for anything
else.  So, the ability to catch the error without incurring a DB call
is a performance gain.  How big?  It is hard to tell.   If nothing
else, this is a better database access pattern.

Change-Id: I8c8bd63b8c755265f4ef75eb2d3e75b9638d52c8

commit_message:
Relax apache min version and pin max version

Before this patch the module pinned its apache dependency to >=1.1.2
which is not a real version number. The next higher version is 1.2.0
which contains a bugfix that will break horizon's redirect
functionality (see https://bugs.launchpad.net/puppet-horizon/+bug/1390453).
This patch relaxes the minimum version to be over 1.0.0 but pins the
major version to be less than 1.2.0 as a stopgap while the bug in the
horizon module is fixed.

Change-Id: If12dfbb2d3c814f36f4d2e787434f90b7dc21cf4

commit_message:
Release 5.0.0 - Juno

Changes in this release:
* Stable Juno release
* Added tags to all nova packages
* Added parameter dhcp_domain to nova class
* Updated the [glance] and [neutron] section parameters for Juno
* Fixed potential duplicate declaration errors for sysctl::value in nova::network
* Fixed dependency cycle in nova::migration::libvirt
* Updated the libvirtd init script path for Debian
* Added parameters for nova service validation to nova::api
* Added nova::policy to control policy.json
* Fixed the rabbit_virtual_host default in nova::cells
* Bumped stdlib dependency to >=4.0.0
* Added force_raw_images parameter to nova::compute class
* Replaced usage of the keyword type with the string 'type' since type is a reserved keyword in puppet 3.7
* Added parameter ec2_workers to nova::api
* Fixed bug in usage of --vlan versus --vlan_start in nova_network provider
* Added parameter rabbit_ha_queues to nova class
* Added parameter pool to nova_floating type
* Added parameters to control whether to configure keystone users
* Added nova::cron::archive_deleted_rows class to create a crontab for archiving deleted database rows
* Changed the keystone_service to only be configured if the endpoint is to be configured
* Added parameter keystone_ec2_url to nova::api
* Added the ability to override the keystone service name in ceilometer::keystone::auth
* Removed dynamic scoping of File resources in nova class
* Add parameter workers to in nova::conductor and deprecate conductor_workers in nova::api
* Update nova quota parameters for Juno
* Migrated the ceilometer::db::mysql class to use openstacklib::db::mysql and deprecated the mysql_module parameter
* Removed deprecation notice for sectionless nova_config names

commit_message:
Drop rabbitmq dependency to <4.0.0

The difference in rabbit versions between openstacklib, cinder and nova
causes dependency conflicts. Version 4 of the rabbitmq module dropped
support for setting up erlang. This patch drops the required version to
between 2.0.2 and 4.0.0 in order to line up with the other modules
rather than requiring the other modules to change their dependencies as
well as set up erlang.

Change-Id: I99383b28574958a43b88b4feb0025ad795a6fda2

commit_message:
Always match lowercase MAC

In some places we are making comparisons between MACs
from different sources like:
* from DB - those are lowercase strings
* from other inputs - where we do not know if MAC will
  be lowercase, uppercase (or mixed) string
We need to always lowercase string in DB queries.

Also new utils function was created: is_same_mac to compare
if MACs are equal. It uses netaddr.EUI internally.

Change-Id: Idae5bc6009f857e72712afac04ffe174e73c7a87
Closes-Bug: #1394466
(cherry picked from commit dfe79d35a47a28873f271131cf2fdae7052e0713)

commit_message:
Update i18n translation for ML2 plugin log msg's

All the existing LOG.info, LOG.warning, LOG.error and LOG.critical
messages should have _LI, _LW, _LE and _LC respectively.
 Also, debug level log shouldn't be translated.

This patch set will cover the ml2 directory under neutron/plugins.

Partial-Bug: #1320867
Change-Id: I9d78d23bbc14e7c536c6ddf2dc4f52c67faeb667

commit_message:
Updates to reschedule_router() for DVR

The existing reschedule_router() only paritially supports
multiple agents per router.  For example, _unbind_router()
is called for multiple agents, but only one agent is notified
via router_added_to_agent() after rescheduling is done.

Also, the snat binding needs to removed prior to any
rescheduling.

Change-Id: I56fefb0f3f6253531e11805e365c9f1d98a45c5b
Partial-Bug: #1348309
Partially-implements: blueprint neutron-ovs-dvr

commit_message:
Test that a namespace is created for new routers

This test implements a check to make sure that when creating a new
router which is connected to an internal network, a new namespace in the
format of 'qrouter-<id>' is created.

This is part of the integration tests effort:
 - [1/3] - Add ability to run daemonized Neutron processes
 - [2/3] - Add Integration Tests framework

* Add a flag to policy.Enforcer to control if rules read from policy
config file overwrite existing rule(s) in Enforcer object.

This requirement comes from Glance adoption. In Glance domain model,
before load policy configure file(s) (if needed - force or file update)
ProtectProperty logic domain provided may already added some rules

there instead of always overwrite them by configure files in any case.

loaded rules from configure file(s), without this flag, when a configure
file got changed, reloading will not be triggered when calling

Signed-off-by: Zhi Yan Liu <zhiyanl@cn.ibm.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Add rule overwrite flag to Enforcer class

* Add a flag to policy.Enforcer to control if rules read from policy
config file overwrite existing rule(s) in Enforcer object.

This requirement comes from Glance adoption. In Glance domain model,
before load policy configure file(s) (if needed - force or file update)
ProtectProperty logic domain provided may already added some rules
according to operator configure, so policy.Enforcer need to keep them
there instead of always overwrite them by configure files in any case.

* Fix a minor issue which causes use_conf flag loss once load_rules()
loaded rules from configure file(s), without this flag, when a configure
file got changed, reloading will not be triggered when calling
enforcer().

Change-Id: I6f552dcf37128668abc71f5804ff12902a0e1850
Signed-off-by: Zhi Yan Liu <zhiyanl@cn.ibm.com>

commit_message:
labs: sleep in shutdown_controller.sh

After building the cluster with the two additional snapshots on the
controller VM, we end up with a dying nova-compute service.

Sleeping 2+ seconds after booting into compute and before rebooting
controller fixes the problem: nova-compute keeps running and its status
in nova-manage service list will go to XXX and back to :-) without user
intervention.

Change-Id: I8ba20c77392b0966d6febfc300790cf1943f2ad5

commit_message:
Makes health return True or False

API returns a 204 for the health check with no body content.
The function should have returned  True if http result was a 204,
or else a False.

I solved the problem by making the function return false in case of an
error.

Change-Id: I02771f5aa61db4ed83da952245744cb3a6163a26
Closes-bug: #1288986

commit_message:
Fix for extra_specs KeyError

During _cold_migrate, there is a code path when
extra_specs is not present in the request_spec['instance_type']
bag. Identified one test case where removing extra_specs
causes the same error as reported in the bug below. We
just need to tolerate this by using a default value for pop()

Closes-Bug: #1394569

Change-Id: I9d4d02069322af1a1f0b84c1e86d2e586c6712d8

commit_message:
Added some hacks to ensure lv creating success

* added vgremove right before vgcreate

* inserted udevadm settle before vgremove and vgcreate.
  this is for avoiding udev race when there are
  unhandled events in udev queue

Closes-Bug: 1373435
Change-Id: Ic764bb1722ac45b432fc7c476f6e418a3715ac8a

commit_message:
Fix snapshot-list filter key 'usage'

Manilaclient sends filter key 'usage' with snapshot-list request anytime.
But it is incompatible with juno version of Manila.
Make manilaclient avoid sending this key in case it is not specified
explicitly.

Change-Id: Iada90df5b88848cb4cdb78d1a550e726b8829428
Closes-Bug: #1394974

commit_message:
Release 5.0.0 - Juno

Changes in this release:
* Added class to manage policy.json
* Changed the default value of the san_thin_provision parameter for eqlx
* Added database tuning parameters
* Made keystone user creation optional when creating a service
* Added ability to hide secrets from logs
* Added parameters for netapp and and cinder-api workers
* Corrected the package name for cinder backup
* Added support for the EMC VNX direct driver
* Migrated the mysql backend to use openstacklib::db::mysql
* Added support for availability zone

Change-Id: I08b059778354b9c2280501d8defa2e4884b8f3a7

commit_message:
Always match lowercase MAC

In some places we are making comparisons between MACs
from different sources like:
* from DB - those are lowercase strings
* from other inputs - where we do not know if MAC will
  be lowercase, uppercase (or mixed) string
We need to always lowercase string in DB queries.

Also new utils function was created: is_same_mac to compare
if MACs are equal. It uses netaddr.EUI internally.

Change-Id: Idae5bc6009f857e72712afac04ffe174e73c7a87
Closes-Bug: #1394466

commit_message:
Add heartbeat driver internal API

Some drivers can have to do a heartbeat to detect connection lost
quickly. This change adds a new internal driver API that will be used
by the executor to do the heartbeat, the default implementation of the
heartbeat is a no-op, each driver can reimplements this method to do
additionnal actions, when heartbeat occurs.

Related-Bug: #856764
Related-Bug: #1371723

Change-Id: I1d0200d6d6ed0fd76572c38b2d06aa82a678362d

commit_message:
RabbitMQ heartbeat implementation

AMQP offers a heartbeat feature to ensure that the application layer
promptly finds out about disrupted connections (and also completely
unresponsive peers). If the client requests heartbeats on connection, rabbit
server will regularly send messages to each connections with the
expectation of a response.

Change-Id: I971f6146ed73d8e1a11dcb4012b40676addb3991
Co-Authored-By: Oleksii Zamiatin <ozamiatin@mirantis.com>
Co-Authored-By: Ilya Pekelny<ipekelny@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Redeploy controllers in case ceph-osd added to cluster

Ceph-osd relies on ceph-mon that installed on controllers,
in case controllers were deployed first, without any ceph-osd,
ceph-mon wont be present

If user will try to deploy ceph-osd afterwards - deployment
will fail, because ceph-osd wont be able to connect to ceph-mon
Right now the only option is to reconfigure controllers
in case ceph-osd added to cluster, after introducing granular
deployment it will be possible to execute only necessery task

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: 1388798
Closes-Bug: 1362601

Change-Id: I12e3a2e65d2a08d07f8a0b2845a232695477c587

commit_message:
Release 5.0.0 - Juno

Changes in this release:
* Added ceilometer::policy to control policy.json
* Fixed bug in glance_image type
* Added parameter os_region_name to glance::api
* Added support for vSphere datastore backend
* Updated the calls to the glance command-line utility
* Added parameter swift_store_large_object_size to glance::backend::swift
* Bumped stdlib dependency to >=4.0.0
* Added parameter command_options to glance::cache::cleaner and glance::cache::pruner
* Added parameter package_ensure to glance::backend::rbd
* Added parameter manage_service to various classes
* Added parameters to control whether to configure users
* Migrated the glance::db::mysql class to use openstacklib::db::mysql and deprecated the mysql_module parameter
* Added parameter registery_client_protocol to glance::api
* Fixed ssl parameter requirements for kombu and rabbit

Change-Id: I5dcce1d748602dd46d409d51523b96a51709d285

commit_message:
Drop RpcProxy usage from LBaaS code

Update the LBaaS code to stop using the RpcProxy compatibility class.

commit_message:
Enable filter alarms by their type

Since type is a very important attribute for alarm object, it will be much
convenient to get alarms by certain type. This patch adds the 'alarm_type'
parameter to get_alarms interface to implement it.

End user can filter alarms by using 'type' filter.

NOTE: this patch changes the parameter 'type' to 'alarm_type' in
get_alarm_changes interface of storage module, to keep consistent with
get_alarm interface.

Change-Id: Ib81375028957490f3a114de7627bc4bcb20f3d77

commit_message:
Support query filtering for templates and EDP objects

Allow query params to be passed through the REST API for the
following objects:

* cluster templates
* node group templates
* data sources
* jobs
* job executions
* job binaries
* job binary internals

Suppress an exception when invalid filter fields are used,
simply return empty list.

Change-Id: Ie94a25fb0861cd78589983c6a6c7f36b50598b39
Partial-implements: blueprint enable-result-filtering

Update sahara endpoint type to avoid underscore

"data_processing" -> "data-processing"

Using data_processing causes a problem when defining the endpoint
statically in keystone.

commit_message:
Support query filtering for cluster objects

The cluster_get_all implementation already supports query
parameters internally, but it is not exposed to the UI. Allow
query params to be passed in from the UI. Suppress an exception
when invalid filter fields are used, simply return empty list.
This will be a model for adding filtering to all x_list() methods
in the API.

Partial-implements: blueprint enable-result-filtering
Change-Id: I20a0de3056bb17cee2d55d87a61b2e23b9c4b657

commit_message:
Fix MemberListToMap ValueError with empty list

When parameter with type CommaDelimitedList has
Default value '' and MemberListToMap get member list
like reference to this parameter, it get [u''].
MemberListToMap do wrong parsing of this value: it
should return {} instead of ValueError.

Change-Id: Iaf4bd796fa93d4176afd16de36869375d8a773c4

commit_message:
Set lock_path in cinder.conf

Without this set, interprocess locking does not work properly.

We also need to ensure the cinder state directory is writable
by cinder, up to now it was not.
Change-Id: Idcabf808d5f7255d0cc382b7857a4c13b9b7a2dc
Closes-Bug: 1394963

commit_message:
Enforce log hints in neutron.services.loadbalancer

This change enforces log hints use and removes debug level log
translation, modifications are validated through a hacking rule and
the change respects loggging guidelines.

Validate that hacking rules apply to directories:
    - neutron/services/loadbalancer

Change-Id: I5f2a1a8861728399f3852fc9704eb160c35f7f8d

commit_message:
Fix package name for Fedora-based distributions

The current documentation describe a dependency with libqp-dev
package. This package name can be a misstyped libpq-dev, that
is named postgresql-devel in Fedora-based distributions.

This also happends with libmysqlclient-dev, that is mysql-devel
in Fedora.

Change-Id: Ibc0eed6c27643fbb9d6594688c3c5dd7165b9d58

At the moment we use the following structure:

<clock offset='utc'>
  <timer name='hpet' present='no'/>

To elimintate time drift between virtual instances we are changing

<clock offset='utc'>
  <timer name='rtc' tickpolicy='catchup' track=‘guest'>

</clock>

commit_message:
Change time policy to eliminate time drift

At the moment we use the following structure:

<clock offset='utc'>
  <timer name='hpet' present='no'/>
</clock>

To elimintate time drift between virtual instances we are changing
structure to:

<clock offset='utc'>
  <timer name='rtc' tickpolicy='catchup' track=‘guest'>
    <catchup threshold='123' slew='120' limit='10000’/>
  </timer>
  <timer name='pit' tickpolicy='delay'/>
  <timer name='hpet' present='no'/>
</clock>

Change-Id: I3e00e7cfb11584d484665a9872ee59318e7209e7
Closes-Bug: 1394546

ISO image if md5sum doesn't match and prompts
user to re-run osbash script as oppose to asking
the user to remove the corrupt image.

commit_message:
TEMPEST: refactor error handling while installation

Tempest installation doesn't contain enough information for debugging
errors, which can be occured during installation.

This patch adds:
 - logging failed command and its output to:
   `rally.verification.verifiers.tempest.tempest.check_output`;
 - handling TempestSetupFailure in validation tempest scenarios;
 - fix in hacking check for logging module.

Change-Id: Ida723c6898cb6845459169f387ca36bf280fb644

commit_message:
Remove Mock class monkey patching

Replace use of Mock with Mock(). The Mock class was being modified and
so affecting other tests where Mock is used. An instance of the Mock
class is now used to keep the tests isolated.

Change-Id: Iccab8430d5814258c8c2d1f9af015bce999549bc
Closes-Bug: #1286245

commit_message:
Make 'IP address' field optional for LBaaS VIP creation

Since 'IP address' argument is optional in the CLI command, it
should not be mandatory for the field "Specify a free IP address
from the selected subnet". This patch sets 'required=False' for
this field. Some LBaaS VIP test data cleanup is also done.

Closes-Bug: #1386616

Change-Id: I112919d12ca3b4f40d9b907b7f47b64502d5ae7c

commit_message:
Remove module strutils,timeutils,importutis

We have used oslo.utils in cinder consumer code, and replaced
strutils,timeutils,importutis with oslo.utils. This commit
sync oslo-incubator consumer code and remove them.

commit_message:
transform samples only when transformers exist

the pipeline is oddly setup to loop through each sample and
attempt to transform it even when there are no transformers. this
is madness and should be stopped -- this patch does this.

at best, this should improve performance because of needless
looping, at worst, we get rid of misleading 'tranforming sample'
logs.

Change-Id: I80ba2b7775fda03670c7fa556ad5a779c6eefd27

commit_message:
Drop and recreate FK if adding new PK to routerl3bindings

Since MySQL 5.6 FK columns cannot be altered. As a workaround we can
drop the FK before ALTER COLUMN and then recreate it.

Change-Id: Icd1b3075cf29a6b0c477a4ddea2e6ebee91baef8
Closes-Bug: 1384555

commit_message:
Fix ntpd start on centos in cloud-init boothook

1) Add forgottent ntpd start into centos's cloud-init boothook.

2) Toggle ntp server on ubuntu to be sure it will start with correct
settings.

3) Fix typo in both boothook files
ntp(d) must be stopped before syncing date with ntpdate.

Change-Id: I4e8e912b61a57c84e24e13be10983654bcfec0ab
Closes-Bug: #1394617

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-11-17 10:51:09.000000000', 'files': ['keystoneclient/contrib/auth/v3/saml2.py'], 'message': 'Cache unscoped SAML tokens locally

Federation workflow is too expensive to repeat it for every OpenStack
operation. As long as session objects with saml2 cookies stored inside
are not reused between separate cli calls SAML auth plugins will cache
unscoped federated tokens.
This is a WIP patch proposing storing unencrypted and unsecured patches
as a local files (with permissions set to 0600).

commit_message:
Cache unscoped SAML tokens locally

Federation workflow is too expensive to repeat it for every OpenStack
operation. As long as session objects with saml2 cookies stored inside
are not reused between separate cli calls SAML auth plugins will cache
unscoped federated tokens.
This is a WIP patch proposing storing unencrypted and unsecured patches
as a local files (with permissions set to 0600).
Keyring was checked but it seems like this method also requires manual
password passing and is not suitable for a library use.

Change-Id: I6060f07980aeb34b5d949ccf36ce110ac3335867

commit_message:
Force detach volume

There may be bad situation the volume is attached to a deleted instance,
in this case, we should force detach the instance from volume.
And force detach action is supported by cinder, it's will be helpful
to add this to cinderclient.

Change-Id: I6c2552fad0d8a203cdd7ecc1d1fedf3a6a33ec64
Closes-bug: #1386061

commit_message:
Add package support to ceilometer-alarm-notifier

Updates the ceilometer-alarm-notifier so that it supports
using distro packages via pkg-map and package-installs.
The default distro package is set to openstack-ceilometer-alarm
which on RHEL/Fedora contains the ceilometer-alarm-notifier
binary.

Also, includes the related svc-map configs so that the
packaged version of the systemd scripts work correctly.

Change-Id: I0f40e0e241d3cfa2f2c33164a871792fe1b0bee2

commit_message:
Add debug log when over quota exception occurs

There are some weird logs showed in bug 1353962, with
current logs we can't decide which part is wrong.
Add more logs will help operater to know the real reason
that make the quota exceed.

If this change makes too much log out, after bug 1353962
is fixed, we can talk about remove those logs, but currently
it will be helpful.

Change-Id: I2ab1fb62efc06b1cee213920539980e331870bf5
Related-Bug: #1353962
